'''''Blood Bathory''''' is an [[extended play|EP]] by [[Italy|Italian]] singer [[Alessandro Nunziati|Lord Vampyr]], released in 2007. It is a loose [[concept album]], whose lyrics are based on old [[Hungarian culture|Hungarian]] and [[Folklore of Romania|Romanian]] vampire-related folktales.

The EP's cover references [[Darkthrone]]'s popular 1994 album ''[[Transilvanian Hunger]]'', which itself references [[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]]'s 1993 live album ''[[Live in Leipzig]]''.

